  "original_title": "Clashes between protestors and Sri Lanka army leave 44 protestors, 16 soldiers injured",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Clashes between protestors and Sri Lanka army leave 44 protestors, 16 soldiers injured",
      "author": "Neshella Perera",
      "body_lines": [
        "ECONOMYNEXT \u2013 Friction was seen between anti-government protestors and Sri Lanka\u2019s security forces Wednesday July 13 night leading to a confrontation that left 44 protestors and 16 soldiers hospitalised.",
        "Military Spokesman Nilantha Premaratne told EconomyNext that the clash, that occurred at the Polduwa junction in proximity to Sri Lanka\u2019s parliament complex, left 16 soldiers injured.",
        "Protestors had also taken possession of a soldier\u2019s T-56 firearm and two magazines containing 60 rounds of live ammunition each.",
        "Complaints have been lodged at the Borella police station over the incident and investigations are underway by Welikada and Borella police.",
        "After storming and occupying the prime minister\u2019s office earlier that day, anti-government protestors moved towards Sri Lanka\u2019s parliament and the official residence of the Speaker, demanding Preident Gotabaya Rajapaksa\u2019s letter of resignation and urging Prime Minister Ranil Wickremesinghe to also step down as Acting President.",
        "Several rounds of tear gas and water cannons had been used to disperse the crowd of protestors, preventing a breaching of the police barricades on the way to parliament and the Speaker\u2019s residence.",
        "Meanwhile, an all-party meeting was called for on Wednesday where the security forces had discussed with the Speaker the use of force against protestors. However opposition leaders had refused to consider the request.",
        "Former Army chief Field Marshal Sarath Fonseka advised the security forces to not use force against protestors. The opposition MP urged the army to be lawful and disciplined over the people\u2019s struggle and point their weapons and guns towards \u201ccorrupt politicians\u201d instead. (Colombo/Jul14/2022)"
      ],
